 \frac{(n-1)S^2}{\sigma^2} = \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\sum_{i=1}^n (X_i - \bar X)^2 \sim \chi^2_{n-1},\text{ where }\bar X = \frac{X_1+\cdots+X_n}{n}. 
A,B
\Pr(\chi_{n-1}^2 >B) = \Pr(\chi^2_{n-1}>A) = 0.05/2
\Pr(A < \chi^2_{n-1}<B) = 0.95
 \Pr\left( A < \frac{(n-1)S^2}{\sigma^2} < B \right) = 0.95. 
 \Pr\left( \frac{(n-1)S^2}{B} < \sigma^2 < \frac{(n-1)S^2}{A} \right) =0.95. 
